07","1490":"1490","1417":"1417","1390":"1390","1416":"1416","Ripton, Kent, England":"Kent, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ashford, Kent, England":"Ashford, Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fogge","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Hogg  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hogg","meanings":["English (northern England and Scotland): nickname for a swineherd or shepherd, from Middle English <i>hog(ge)</i> (Old English <i>hogg</i>) denoting either a pig, especially a castrated one, or a young sheep before its first shearing (the latter sense is most likely in northern England).","German (<b>Högg</b>): topographic name, a variant of   Heck   1, found chiefly in Bavaria."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":65,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William Fogge was born about 1390, in England as the son of Sir Thomas Fogge and Joane de Valence. He had at least 1 son with Septvans. His occupation is listed as sheriff in Kent, England."},"et":{"about 1390–":"umbes 1390–Surnud","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1417–1490":"1417–1490","–1407":"–1407","–1420":"–1420","about 1390":"umbes 1390","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1407":"1407","1490":"1490","1417":"1417","1390":"1390","1416":"1416","Ripton, Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ashford, Kent, England":"Ashford, Kent, England"},"fi":{"about 1390–":"noin 1390–Kuollut","1390–Male":"1390–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1417–1490":"1417–1490","–1407":"–1407","–1420":"–1420","about 1390":"noin 1390","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1407":"1407","1490":"1490","1417":"1417","1390":"1390","1416":"1416","Ripton, Kent, England":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Ashford, Kent, England":"Ashford, Kent, England"},"fr":{"about 1390–":"environ 1390–Décédé","1390–Male":"1390–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1390–Female":"1390–Décédée","1417–1490":"1417–1490","–1407":"–1407","–1420":"–1420","about 1390":"environ 1390","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1407":"1407","1490":"1490","1417":"1417","1390":"1390","1416":"1416","Ripton, Kent, England":"Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","Ashford, Kent, England":"Ashford, Kent, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sir William Fogge est né environ 1390, à Angleterre, fils de Sir Thomas Fogge et Joane de Valence. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Septvans. Sa profession de son indiquée est sheriff à Kent, Angleterre."},"de":{"about 1390–":"um 1390–Verstorben","1390–Male":"1390–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1390–Female":"1390–Verstorben","1417–1490":"1417–1490","–1407":"–1407","–1420":"–1420","about 139